The White House will be holding a roundtable on the 37th anniversary of Title IX. The roundtable will feature Senior Advisor Valerie Jarrett, Education Secretary Arne Duncan, and women athletes and scientists. Participants include Billie Jean King and Dominique Dawes. 30 local high school girls will be in the audience along with professional athletes and Title IX advocates. The event will be streamed live on WhiteHouse.gov and on a Facebook application. Non-Facebook users can submit comments and questions through a special comment form. The roundtable will be held on June 23 at 2:30 PM EDT in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. After the roundtable, Billie Jean King, Dominique Dawes, and others will hold a media availability at the West Wing. Media can RSVP to attend the event.